      "message": "Thanks for the review.\n\nMy argument was that it\u0027d have to cover the same number of different cases with introducing additional vars to find answers for the following questions.\n1) are the buffered lines from the previous or current entry?\n2) are the buffered lines partial or complete lines?\n\nIn the snippet, add() takes `ts` to answer (1), but multiple LogEntries could have the same TimeOffset. (or, all of them could omit TimeOffset)\n\nI\u0027m sure the snippet can be updated to implement all the business requirements, but IMO, it will end up with having the same complexity as this does. In this latest patchset, I polished the code as you suggested and it looks better, I think.",
